Explicitly release renderer objects when Rutabaga is dropped.

Normal virtio-gpu commands unreference individual resources, but VMM shutdown
may leave resources and contexts in Rutabaga's maps. Merely dropping the Rust
maps does not call the renderer's resource-unref entry point. Drain them while
the renderer component is still alive so gfxstream can free Vulkan allocations
through the driver's normal unbind path before stream_renderer_teardown closes
the DRM file.

--- a/src/rutabaga_core.rs
+++ b/src/rutabaga_core.rs
@@ -1286,4 +1286,12 @@ impl Rutabaga {
 }
 
+impl Drop for Rutabaga {
+    fn drop(&mut self) {
+        if let Err(e) = self.destroy_objects() {
+            log::error!("failed to clean up Rutabaga objects during shutdown: {e}");
+        }
+    }
+}
+
